{
  "texts": [
    "Aligner nets were not used for coarse alignment as applying Online Finetuner to such coarse resolutions was computationally cheap, and also the 8192 nm aligner tended to overfit to the training dataset.",
    "This method was able to correct all of the non-affine deformations in the main island, but produced bad alignment for small islands that couldn't be adequately represented at 8192 nm resolution.",
    "In order to handle both cases, two independent alignment versions were produced for each islandone using the Online Finetunner approach and the other using affine alignment.",
    "The alignment version that produced higher similarity to v14 was chosen for the final alignment.",
    "Similarity was calculated by applying Multiscale-SSIM 34."
  ]
}